Manchester United host Tottenham Hotspur in the Premier League on Wednesday night. The Red Devils could only draw 2-2 with Aston Villa at Old Trafford three days prior. However, this game takes on a different level of importance, as Jose Mourinho will be returning to United as Tottenham Hotspur manager. Spurs are currently two points ahead of Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s men in fifth place. Kick off is 8.30pm West African time. Man United XI vs Tottenham: De Gea, Wan Bissaka, Lindelof, Maguire, Young, McTominay, Fred, James, Lingard, Rashford, Greenwood Tottenham XI vs Man United: Gazzaniga, Aurier, Sanchez, Alderweireld, Vertonghen, Winks, Sissoko, Lucas Moura, Alli, Son, Kane Wednesday, December 4 Full time: Manchester United have defeated Tottenham 2-1. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.